HEADWORD: Triploblastic
<hw>Trip`lo*blas"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
threefold + <ets>-blast + -ic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Of,
pertaining to, or designating, that condition of the ovum in which there
are three primary germinal layers, or in which the blastoderm splits
into three layers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Triploidite</ent>⟦br⟧
